name: float_f64_epsilon
description: |
  This is binary64 machine epsilon, 2^-52: the gap between 1 and the next
  representable value above 1. It catches code that assumes a universal
  epsilon across float widths or uses epsilon as an absolute tolerance at every
  magnitude.
format: hex
decode-as: f64-le
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f64"
  - "epsilon"
  - "precision"
---
00 00 00 00 00 00 b0 3c   # 0x3cb0000000000000: 2^-52
